## Task 2 — Your First Blink (Using Variables)

### Question 1. Why do we put `pinMode(ledPin, OUTPUT);` inside `setup()` and not inside `loop()`?

We place `pinMode(ledPin, OUTPUT);` inside `setup()` because the pin only needs to be configured once when the board starts up. Putting it inside `loop()` would repeatedly configure the pin, which is unnecessary and inefficient.

### Question 2. What would happen if we removed both `delay()` calls?

I predicted that without the delays, the LED would switch between ON and OFF extremely fast—faster than the human eye can perceive. After testing it, I observed that the LED appeared to remain continuously ON, although it looked slightly dimmer because it was switching states very rapidly.

